('unilag','Use of English','Oral English and Phonology',NULL,'What is the function of pause in spoken English?','To separate words','To separate phrases','To separate clauses and indicate the organization of ideas','To separate sentences','C','Pause is an essential aspect of spoken English, and it serves to separate clauses, indicate the organization of ideas, and provide time for the speaker to breathe and plan their next utterance.','easy',true,false,NOW()),
