('unilag','Use of English','Oral English and Phonology',NULL,'What is the difference between a monophthong and a diphthong?','A monophthong is a combination of two vowel sounds, while a diphthong is a single vowel sound','A monophthong is a single vowel sound, while a diphthong is a combination of two vowel sounds','A monophthong is a consonant sound, while a diphthong is a vowel sound','A monophthong is a vowel sound, while a diphthong is a consonant sound','B','A monophthong is a single, pure vowel sound, while a diphthong is a combination of two vowel sounds pronounced in a single syllable, with the sound gliding from one vowel to another.','hard',true,false,NOW()),
('unilag','Use of English','Oral English and Phonology',NULL,'Which of the following is an example of a free variation in speech?','The pronunciation of ''either'' as /ˈaɪðər/ or /ˈiːðər/','The pronunciation of ''data'' as /ˈdætə/ or /ˈdeɪtə/','The pronunciation of ''schedule'' as /ˈskɛdʒuːl/ or /ˈʃɛdjuːl/','All of the above','D','Free variation refers to the phenomenon where a word or phrase can be pronounced in more than one way, without any change in meaning or social significance. The examples provided are all instances of free variation in speech.','hard',true,false,NOW()),
